      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those unpredictable RAM spikes are often related to Python's garbage collector running, which tries to free up memory when it deems objects are no longer needed. However, with huge datasets, it could also be Pandas internally caching data or inefficiently handling large intermediate operations during iteration. If the spikes persist after using generators, try batch processing the data or explicitly managing when intermediate data structures are cleared.",
